    <text type="letter"> 
        <body>
            <opener>
                <name type="place">Camden</name><ptr target="tex.00479_n1"/>
                <dateline><date when="1891-08-01"><choice><choice><abbr>evn'g</abbr><expan>evening</expan></choice> 
                    <abbr>Aug:</abbr><expan>August</expan></choice> 1 '91</date></dateline>
           <salute>Dearest sister,</salute>  
            </opener>
                <p>I have just a minute before the mail &#38; <choice><abbr>enc:</abbr><expan>enclosed</expan></choice> &#36;5&#8212;makes 
                    me uneasy &#38; wretched [e]nough <choice><abbr>ab't</abbr><expan>about</expan></choice> <choice><abbr>y'r</abbr><expan>your</expan></choice> 
                    sickness<ptr target="tex.00479_n2"/> &#38; c:&#8212;hope &#38; pray you may be easy 
                    by this time reaches you&#8212;I hope Dr B[ingham]<ptr target="tex.00479_n3"/> will write 
                    to me forth&#8211;with if convenient<ptr target="tex.00479_n4"/>&#8212;</p>
                <p>Best love to you, sister dear&#8212;</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer> 
        </body>
    </text>
